## What is Unit 2 about?

Unit 2 of AP Human Geography studies how people are distributed across the planet, why populations grow or shrink, and why people move from one place to another. You'll learn the demographic transition model (DTM), how to read population pyramids, the difference between Malthusian and Boserup theories, and the factors that drive migration. This unit makes up about 12–17% of the exam and is one of the most FRQ-heavy units — every recent AP HUG exam has tested at least one population or migration concept in depth.

