## Common AP exam mistakes

- **Confusing CBR with TFR** — CBR is births per 1,000 people; TFR is children per woman
- **Mixing up Stage 2 and Stage 3** — Stage 2 has falling death rates and high births; Stage 3 has falling births
- **Forgetting Stage 5 exists** — countries like Japan and Germany have populations declining
- **Calling Malthus right** — Malthus predicted famine that didn't happen (Boserup explains why)
- **Mixing up refugees and asylum seekers** — refugees are designated; asylum seekers are applying
- **Treating migration as one-way** — Ravenstein's laws say every stream has a counter-stream

